reviews.review_text:
Lesh Filling Very good show folks, on of the more rocking ones for 1980.   Every one of them are on this night.

The sound quality, just phenomonal.   

Great Stella, Minglewood (one of my favorite versions) and a classic Loser.   If you don't know 1980, this is the place to start.

Jerry is on fire Jerry rips it up and rolls on every solo.  The rest of the band can hardly keep up with him, right up to to the encore when Bobby goes to sing after Jerry's solo but Jerry's not done yet and Bobby has to back off and start again.  Loved listening to this. Wild show.

Great audience recording- excellent work; thank you!  Crystal clear sound and well balanced mix, with an appreciative crowd in the background.
5-2-80 Incredible audience recording/remaster. Excellent performance too!
Jerry was on fire in early '80 This is a great performance by Jerry and an excellent recording
